Package: chemfuse
Title: Multi-Database Cheminformatics Suite
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Junguk", "Hur", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "junguk.hur@med.und.edu",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: R interface to ChemFuse, integrating PubChem, ChEMBL, UniChem,
    BindingDB, Open Targets, and SureChEMBL with local ADMET prediction and
    analysis. Provides functions for compound search, batch screening,
    cross-database identifier mapping, molecular descriptor calculation, and
    ADMET property prediction via a reticulate bridge to the Python chemfuse
    package.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.34),
    tibble,
    jsonlite
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    readr
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.11), chemfuse Python package
    (https://pypi.org/project/chemfuse/)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.0
URL: https://github.com/hurlab/ChemFuse
BugReports: https://github.com/hurlab/ChemFuse/issues
